## Germplasm Phenotype:
   - [CS340424]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;Reduced seed coat mucilage.
   - [spi-11]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;Trichome cells have shorter branches, reduced stalk length and width.  Epidermal pavement cells are less complex, with less lobing.  Root hairs are shorter and root hair vacuoles are fragmented.
   - [spi-12]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;Trichome cells have shorter branches, reduced stalk length and width.  Epidermal pavement cells are less complex, with less lobing.  Root hairs are shorter and root hair vacuoles are fragmented.

   - [spi-4.2]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;Trichome cells have shorter branches, reduced stalk length and width.  Epidermal pavement cells are less complex, with less lobing.  Root hairs are shorter and root hair vacuoles are fragmented.
   - [spi-4/lip5-1]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;Significant reduction in seed coat mucilage. On a subcellular level there are defects in vacuolar trafficking.
